# PR Lifecycle

## Creating

1. Commit with a descriptive conventional-commit message.
2. Push: `git push -u origin HEAD`
3. Open PR: `gh pr create` with summary and test plan.

## CI Monitoring

1. Poll: `gh pr checks <PR-NUMBER>` until all checks complete.
2. On failure, read logs: `gh run view <RUN-ID> --job <JOB-ID> --log-failed`
3. Fix in the worktree, commit, push, re-monitor.
4. If failure is unrelated (e.g. billing/infra), note it and proceed.

## Copilot Review

1. Request: `gh api repos/{owner}/{repo}/pulls/{number}/requested_reviewers --method POST -f 'reviewers[]=copilot'`
2. Poll for review: `gh api repos/{owner}/{repo}/pulls/{number}/reviews --jq '.[-1] | {author: .user.login, state: .state}'`
3. Fetch inline comments: `gh api repos/{owner}/{repo}/pulls/{number}/comments`
4. Fix comments, push, re-request review.

## Merging

- Squash merge: `gh pr merge <number> --squash --body "..."`
- After merge: `git checkout main && git pull`

## Checklist (complete ALL before finishing)

- [ ] `make validate` passes
- [ ] `make test` passes
- [ ] `make test-integration` passes
- [ ] PR created with summary
- [ ] CI checks green (or confirmed unrelated failure)
- [ ] PR URL and status reported to user
